Sentencas: Gadolinia-doped ceria (Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95, GDC) electrolyte was fabricated by aqueous-based tape casting method for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Nanostructured Gd-CeO2 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cell by aqueous tape casting

Sentencas: The ceramic powder prepared by combustion synthesis was used with poly acrylic acid (PAA), poly vinyl alcohol (PVA), poly ethylene glycol (PEG), Octanol, 2,4,7,9-tetramethyl-5-decyne-4,7-diol ethoxylate and double distilled water as dispersant, binder, plasticizer, defoamer, surfactant and solvent respectively, to prepare stable GDC slurry.
Titulo: Nanostructured Gd-CeO2 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cell by aqueous tape casting

Sentencas: The conditions for preparing stable GDC slurries were studied and optimized by sedimentation, zeta potential and viscosity measurements.
Titulo: Nanostructured Gd-CeO2 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cell by aqueous tape casting

Sentencas: Green tapes with smooth surface, flexibility, thickness in the range of 0.35-0.4 mm and 45% relative green density were prepared.
Titulo: Nanostructured Gd-CeO2 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cell by aqueous tape casting

Sentencas: Conventional and flash sintering techniques were used and compared for densification which demonstrated the possibility of surpassing sintering at high temperatures and retarding related grain growth.
Titulo: Nanostructured Gd-CeO2 electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cell by aqueous tape casting
